@*
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
    BnModalDemo — Phase 7.4 (design §"The proof surface"), route "/modal",
    mount-registry key "BnModalDemo". Authored in .razor.

    An EIGHTH page, same rationale as the fourth through seventh: the
    existing pages' frame tables and goldens ARE the parity contracts, and
    the phase that introduces the overlay does not get to rewrite them. This
    page's numbers are ITS OWN contract — asserted by BnModalDemoTests (the
    .NET golden) and by Gates 2/3 on the AVD and the iOS simulator.

    ── THE PAGE ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────

      [0] trigger  BnButton "Show modal" — flips _visible true
      [1] box A    BnView 220×48 (DECLARED — the anchor's sibling ABOVE)
      [2] BnModal  @bind-Visible; content box DECLARED 280×180, padding 12,
                   white; ChildContent:
                     [0] the echo BnText  (Echo(_switched) — the multi-hop
                                           bind proof INSIDE the overlay)
                     [1] BnSwitch bound   @bind-Checked (initially false)
                     [2] BnActivityIndicator   (inside the modal)
                     [3] dismiss BnButton "Dismiss" — sets _visible false
      [3] box B    BnView 220×48 (DECLARED — the anchor's sibling BELOW)
      [4] BnActivityIndicator             (on the page)
      [5] back row BnRow W=300 → BnButton "← Back" (nav parity, LAST — a
                   font-dependent height never sits above a frame assertion)

    THE MODAL SITS BETWEEN TWO DECLARED-SIZE SIBLINGS on purpose: the
    anchor's zero-footprint rule (the THIRD index-mapping rule) is a frame
    assertion on this page, not a comment — boxes A and B hold the EXACT
    frames they hold with Visible=false, or the anchor leaked size into the
    flex flow. The indicator appears in BOTH hosting contexts (page and
    overlay — decision 5's cheap win, proven in both).

    ── WHAT THE THREE SURFACES ASSERT ───────────────────────────────────────
    .NET golden (BnModalDemoTests): the closed mount (no modal wire presence,
    5 root children), the SHOW frame (the modal create AT INSERT INDEX 2 —
    the anchor's slot — with scrimColor, the content box's declared 280×180,
    the four attaches), the HIDE frame (the modal's remove + the four nested
    components' disposal removes, nothing outside the subtree), the
    switch-inside round-trip re-rendering the echo, scrim-tap dismisses vs
    content-tap does not, and re-show = re-create with BOUND state intact.
    On-device (Gates 2/3): the scrim = the root's own bounds, content
    centered at (W−280)/2 × (H−180)/2, the overlay LAST at the root, the
    sibling frames unchanged, the indicator's intrinsic size by oracle, the
    overlay count back to 0 after hide, Android back dismiss-requests.

    Nav parity with every other page: "← Back" → INavigationManager → "/".
    Reachable by mount-name ("BnModalDemo") and by route ("/modal"); no
    button on BnDemo points here. Android's DEEP_LINK_COMPONENTS line is
    Gate 2's.
    ─────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────────
*@
<BnColumn>
    @* [0] the trigger — the only way this page SHOWS the modal. *@
    <BnButton Label="Show modal" OnClick="Show" />

    @* [1]/[3] the declared-size siblings AROUND the modal — the anchor's
       zero-footprint rule as a frame assertion (file header). *@
    <BnView Width="@SiblingWidth" Height="@SiblingHeight" BackgroundColor="#336699" />

    @* [2] the modal — between the siblings, content box DECLARED 280×180. *@
    <BnModal @bind-Visible="_visible"
             ContentWidth="@ContentWidth" ContentHeight="@ContentHeight"
             Padding="@ContentPaddingDp" BackgroundColor="@ContentBackground">
        <BnText Text="@EchoText" />
        <BnSwitch @bind-Checked="_switched" />
        <BnActivityIndicator />
        <BnButton Label="Dismiss" OnClick="Dismiss" />
    </BnModal>

    <BnView Width="@SiblingWidth" Height="@SiblingHeight" BackgroundColor="#66AA33" />

    @* [4] the indicator in its SECOND hosting context (the page itself). *@
    <BnActivityIndicator />

    @* [5] nav parity — measured leaf LAST (the BnFormDemo discipline). *@
    <BnRow Width="@BackRowWidth">
        <BnButton Label="← Back" OnClick="GoBack" />
    </BnRow>
</BnColumn>

@code {
    // ── THE PAGE'S NUMBERS, AS CONSTANTS (the BnScrollDemo discipline) ────────
    //
    // BnModalDemoTests asserts these off the WIRE (never transcribed), and
    // Gates 2/3 read them for the device assertions — one source of truth.

    /// <summary>The content box's DECLARED size — the design's 280 × 180,
    /// asserted cross-platform; centering against the root is host-derived
    /// and asserted per-platform (the 6.3 oracle discipline).</summary>
    internal const int ContentWidthDp = 280;

    /// <inheritdoc cref="ContentWidthDp"/>
    internal const int ContentHeightDp = 180;

    /// <summary>The content box's declared padding.</summary>
    internal const float ContentPaddingDp = 12f;

    /// <summary>The content box's background — opaque, so the scrim behind it
    /// is visibly the SCRIM in every screenshot.</summary>
    internal const string ContentBackground = "#FFFFFF";

    /// <summary>The declared-size siblings around the modal (file header:
    /// the anchor's zero-footprint rule as a frame assertion).</summary>
    internal const int SiblingWidthDp = 220;

    /// <inheritdoc cref="SiblingWidthDp"/>
    internal const int SiblingHeightDp = 48;

    /// <summary>The back row's declared width — every page's nav row shape.</summary>
    internal const int BackRowWidthDp = 300;

    /// <summary>The bound switch's INITIAL state — what the first show frame
    /// carries and what <see cref="Echo"/> starts from.</summary>
    internal const bool InitialSwitched = false;

    /// <summary>The echo line, formatted ONCE for every surface — wire-cased
    /// bools (the change payloads' own vocabulary), the BnFormDemo pattern.</summary>
    internal static string Echo(bool sw) => sw ? "sw:true" : "sw:false";

    private bool _visible;
    private bool _switched = InitialSwitched;

    private string EchoText => Echo(_switched);

    private static readonly string ContentWidth =
        ContentWidthDp.ToString(System.Globalization.CultureInfo.InvariantCulture);

    private static readonly string ContentHeight =
        ContentHeightDp.ToString(System.Globalization.CultureInfo.InvariantCulture);

    private static readonly string SiblingWidth =
        SiblingWidthDp.ToString(System.Globalization.CultureInfo.InvariantCulture);

    private static readonly string SiblingHeight =
        SiblingHeightDp.ToString(System.Globalization.CultureInfo.InvariantCulture);

    private static readonly string BackRowWidth =
        BackRowWidthDp.ToString(System.Globalization.CultureInfo.InvariantCulture);

    private void Show() => _visible = true;

    /// <summary>The app's OWN dismiss (design decision 2's third trigger):
    /// ordinary state, the same unmount path the scrim tap's request takes
    /// once the bound parent writes it back.</summary>
    private void Dismiss() => _visible = false;

    [Inject] public INavigationManager Navigation { get; set; } = default!;

    private Task GoBack() => Navigation.NavigateToAsync("/").AsTask();
}
